ttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/Q1juDisOImE/maxresdefault.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSoVbeOhawHMw0tfztNeEtsXFtLEXKC56yzmA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:720;s:6:"height";i:1280;s:6:"source";s:43:"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q1juDisOImE";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.youtube.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:58:{i:0;s:217:"Cyclohexane chair conformation wedge dash Start by drawing the wedge-dash notation for cis-12-diethylcyclohexane which looks like this Notice that the two ethyl groups are placed on wedges on carbon 1 and on carbon 2.";i:1;s:121:"This is because the molecule is cis which essentially means that both these groups must be either on wedges or on dashes.";i:2;s:80:"Alkanes Introduction To 3d Structures Alkanes Are Drawing Chair Conformations A.";i:3;s:79:"Which wedge-and-dash drawing correctly represents the chair conformation given.";i:4;s:53:"Molecule CH ci CH Chair conformations CH CH H H H н.";i:5;s:42:"H CI CH H H 1 3 HC H H HC CI H CH CI сн.";i:6;s:32:"H 2 Select an answer and submit.";i:7;s:70:"For keyboard navigation use the updown arrow keys to select an answer.";i:8;s:200:"So if you drew a wedge in position 1 and a dash in position 2 it would mean that they are on the same plane - either both axial or both equatorial - assuming that the ring was in a chair conformation.";i:9;s:133:"However if the objective is to show the structural isomers very clearly it may be better to use either the chair conformation sketch.";i:10;s:117:"The chair conformation has alternating axial up axial down so once you have that single axial substituent move on to.";i:11;s:82:"Alternate your axial substituents up and down all the way around your cyclohexane.";i:12;s:43:"Every carbon on the chair conformation has.";i:13;s:101:"Wedgedotted line convention to show the proper stereochemistry indicated in the name of the compound.";i:14;s:67:"Number the carbon atoms in the cyclohexane structure that you draw.";i:15;s:106:"Draw two templates that represents the two chair conformations of cyclohexane and number the carbon atoms.";i:16;s:46:"All cyclohexanes have two chair conformations.";i:17;s:137:"Level three is recognizing cis and trans on a cyclohexane ring and understanding that up substituents can be equatorial as well as axial.";i:18;s:123:"Its important to realize that a chair flip does not turn a wedge into a dash but instead turns an axial into an equatorial.";i:19;s:169:"A wedge and dash projection is a drawing a means of representing a molecule in which three types of lines are used in order to represent the three-dimensional structure.";i:20;s:66:"Solid lines to represent bonds that are in the plane of the paper.";i:21;s:58:"Dashed lines to represent bonds that extend away from the.";i:22;s:50:"Which Wedge-and-dash Drawing Correctly Represents.";i:23;s:32:"Chemistry questions and answers.";i:24;s:82:"Which Wedge-and-dash Drawing Correctly Represents The Chair Conformation Of Given.";i:25;s:55:"Ive seen chair conformation defined in that way before.";i:26;s:47:"That is the specific structure for cyclohexane.";i:27;s:86:"However other cycloalkanes like cyclodecane for example also has a chair conformation.";i:28;s:114:"The chair reference is just referring to the repeating zig-zag shape across the longitudinal axis of the molecule.";i:29;s:158:"This organic chemistry video tutorial provides a basic introduction into drawing the chair conformation of cyclohexane and identifying the most stable confor.";i:30;s:391:"Lets get some practice drawing it chair confirmations one way to do it is to start by drawing two parallel lines that are offset from each others let me go ahead and show you what I mean so heres heres one line and then here is another line theyre parallel to each other but theyre offset a little bit next were going to draw two horizontal dotted lines so the top horizontal dotted line is.";i:31;s:85:"For the conformation with both Cl substituents equatorial draw each of the following.";i:32;s:23:"Wedge and Dash drawing.";i:33;s:23:"Wedge and Dash drawing.";i:34;s:23:"Wedge and Dash drawing.";i:35;s:104:"C6 C3 C5 C1 C2 C4 are hidden in this view Two hydrogens are shown here with stereochemistry you wouldnt.";i:36;s:43:"Chair conformation is 3D as drawn on paper.";i:37;s:173:"So while a wedge is always drawn as up in the chair conformation in the book you can just turn the page upside down and it is now down but obviously still the same molecule.";i:38;s:102:"Wedge and dash is 2D representation of a 3D object so you cant just turn things upside down obviously.";i:39;s:101:"If you are looking for Drawing chair conformations from wedge and dash youve come to the right place.";i:40;s:77:"We have collect images about Drawing chair conformations from wedge and dash.";i:41;s:163:"To summarize remember in the E2 reaction of cyclohexanes only the hydrogen opposite to the leaving group wedgedash or dashwedge can participate in the elimination.";i:42;s:40:"The rate of E2 reaction of cyclohexanes.";i:43;s:147:"How fast a given cyclohexane undergoes E2 elimination depends on how stable the chair conformation with the leaving group in the axial position is.";i:44;s:73:"Next we have to visualize the cyclohexane ring in the chair conformation.";i:45;s:215:"Remember that the skeleton image shown above is more conveniently drawn but loses the 3 rd dimension information so you have to put it back in the chair to determine which should be bolded and which should be wedge.";i:46;s:134:"Wedge-dash diagrams Usually drawn with two bonds in the plane of the page one infront and one behind to give the molecule perspective.";i:47;s:134:"When drawing wedge-dash it is a good idea to visualise the tetrahedral arrangement of the groups and try to make the diagram fit this.";i:48;s:68:"Drawing cyclohexane so that it looks like a chair can be the key to.";i:49;s:110:"The first step in drawing the chair conformation for cis1bromo3methylcyclohexane is to analyze what cis means.";i:50;s:90:"The easiest way to explain what cis means is to look at the compounds wedge-dash notation.";i:51;s:118:"If two groups are on a wedge which means that they are coming out of the plane of the page they are said to be cis or.";i:52;s:35:"Draw the chair form of cyclohexane.";i:53;s:113:"Draw the following molecules twice once using the chair conformation AND once using the wedge and dash depiction.";i:54;s:166:"12 cis-dimethylcyclohexane 12 trans-dibromocyclohexane 13 cis-dichlorocyclohexane 13 trans-dimethylcyclohexane 14 cis-dimethylcyclohexane 14 trans-dibromocyclohexane.";i:55;s:79:"A trisubstituted cyclohexane compound is given below in its chair conformation.";i:56;s:119:"Draw the corresponding planar overhead representation using wedge-and-dash bonds to indicate the substituent positions.";i:57;s:85:"To be graded properly include the hydrogen atoms on the halogen-bearing carbon atoms.";}}